.TH "NAVIGATEEVENT.HASHCHANGE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigateEvent.hashChange \- NavigateEvent: hashChange property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hashChange\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] interface returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if the
navigation is a fragment navigation (i.e., to a fragment identifier in
the same document), or \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.SH VALUE
A boolean value\(em\f[CR]true\f[R] if the navigation is a fragment
navigation, \f[CR]false\f[R] if not.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Some navigations, e.g. cross\-origin navigations, we\f[R]
  \f[I]// cannot intercept. Let the browser handle those normally.\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (!event.canIntercept) {
    \f[B]return\f[R];
  }

  \f[I]// Don\(aqt intercept fragment navigations or downloads.\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (event.hashChange || event.downloadRequest !== \f[B]null\f[R]) {
    \f[B]return\f[R];
  }

  event.intercept({
    handler() {
      \f[B]if\f[R] (event.formData) {
        processFormDataAndUpdateUI(event.formData, event.signal);
      } \f[B]else\f[R] {
        doSinglePageAppNav(event.destination, event.signal);
      }
    },
  });
});
.EE
